TITLE: Handling SearchStarting Event in C#
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to handle the SearchStarting event to modify search behavior, such as dividing the search text into separate terms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/maui-docs/blob/master/controls/datagrid/search-as-you-type.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
private void OnSearchStarting(object sender, DataGridSearchStartingEventArgs e)
{
    string[] terms = e.SearchTerms[0].Split(' ');
    e.SearchTerms.Clear();
    foreach (var term in terms)
    {
        e.SearchTerms.Add(term);
    }
    e.SearchTermsLogicalOperator = LogicalOperator.Or;
}
```

