TITLE: Defining ListView GroupHeaderTemplate in XAML
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to define a custom GroupHeaderTemplate for a .NET MAUI ListView. The DataTemplate contains a Grid with labels to display the group's key and an expand/collapse indicator. The expand/collapse indicator uses a DataTrigger to change its text based on the `IsExpanded` property of the group.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/maui-docs/blob/master/controls/listview/grouping/customize-group-header.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: XAML
CODE:
```
<DataTemplate x:Key="ListViewGroupHeaderTemplate">
    <Grid>
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto" />
            <ColumnDefinition />
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <Label Text="&#x25B8;" Margin="8, 12, 0, 6" TextColor="DarkGray" FontSize="Medium">
            <Label.Triggers>
                <DataTrigger TargetType="Label" Binding="{Binding IsExpanded}" Value="True">
                    <Setter Property="Text" Value="&#x25BE;" />
                </DataTrigger>
            </Label.Triggers>
        </Label>
        <Label Margin="0, 12, 0, 6" Text="{Binding Key}" Grid.Column="1" TextColor="DarkGray" FontSize="Medium" HorizontalOptions="Start" />
    </Grid>
</DataTemplate>
```

