TITLE: Defining DataGrid and Control in XAML
DESCRIPTION: This XAML code snippet demonstrates how to define a DataGrid and a switch control in XAML. The DataGrid is bound to the `Data` property of the `ViewModel`, and the `CanUserReorderColumns` property is bound to the `IsToggled` property of the switch.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/maui-docs/blob/master/controls/datagrid/columns/reordering.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: XAML
CODE:
```
<ContentPage
    x:Class="DataGridMAUI.MainPage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
    xmlns:local="clr-namespace:DataGridMAUI"
    xmlns:telerik="http://schemas.telerik.com/2022/xaml/maui"
    x:Name="page">

    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <local:ViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <Grid RowDefinitions="Auto,*">
        <Switch
            HorizontalOptions="Center"
            IsToggled="{Binding CanUserReorderColumns, Mode=TwoWay}"
            VerticalOptions="Center" />

        <telerik:RadDataGrid
            x:Name="dataGrid"
            Grid.Row="1"
            ItemsSource="{Binding Data}"
            CanUserReorderColumns="True" />
    </Grid>
</ContentPage>
```

