TITLE: Defining Sample Model and ViewModel in C# for DataGrid
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet provides a simple model and ViewModel setup for populating the DataGrid with sample data. It includes an ObservableCollection of data items used as the DataGrid's ItemsSource, facilitating dynamic UI binding and interaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/telerik/maui-docs/blob/master/knowledge-base/datagrid-maui-cell-content-template-selector.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public class ViewModel
{
    public ObservableCollection<Data> Items { get; set; }
    public ViewModel()
    {

        this.Items = new ObservableCollection<Data>()
        {
                new Data { Country = "India", Capital = "New Delhi"},
                new Data { Country = "South", Capital = "Cape Town"},
                new Data { Country = "Nigeria", Capital = "Abuja"},
                new Data { Country = "Singapore", Capital = "Singapore"}
        };
    }
}
public class Data
{
    public string Country { get; set; }
    public string Capital { get; set; }
}
```

